Second batch of Nigerians evacuated by the federal government from the war-ravaged Ukraine arrived Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja, on Friday evening. The returnees arrived aboard Air Peace from Poland, conveying over 180 Nigerian citizens.
The first batch of returnees aboard Max Air arrived earlier on Friday from Romania.
The returnees were given $100 each by the federal government to facilitate their way back home in the various states of the federation.
 
